<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17170&amp;p=215673#p215673"><![CDATA[
Or if it can be more expensive but also alot better, try SD2SNES.<br /><br />Making multi carts of SMW Hacks (I assume that's what you want) wouldn't work out as well as most of them are around 4MB which would require a 27c322/29F032/29F033 for ONE game. <br /><br />Making a multi cart would require something like a 29GL128 + proper level shifting as well as a 74HC161 to decode the highest address lines (A21 and A22 since we can have to up 4x 4MB games on the 29GL128 as it holds 16MB of data) to switch the games based on reset.<br /><br />You'll need custom made adapters/boards for that so I suggest an Evedrive/PowerPak or SD2SNES as well.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6594">Ice Man</a> — Thu Mar 22, 2018 8:32 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
