<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17170&amp;p=215661#p215661"><![CDATA[
Hey, is the OP asking about SNES or NES multicarts?? It's very hard to answer both at the same time. Either way I believe NES has been answered well enough already, so I can say SNES idea is essentially the same. One of the easiest ways to do a multicart is by switching it by reset and you can do the same for SNES games, although you can't mix &quot;mappers&quot;, so you can't mix Lorom with Hirom games (just easily) on 1 cart. You should also keep in mind whether your games use SRAM save, although this is also doable to install a bigger SRAM chip and switch it the same way as program chips so all games have independent save files<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3986">MaarioS</a> — Thu Mar 22, 2018 4:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
