<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: How to make multicartes a particular program to use or a]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17170&amp;p=215640#p215640"><![CDATA[
For me, the easiest multicart to do is a reset based.<br />You can take a look on the one I've donte <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=28&amp;t=15072" class="postlink">here.</a><br />It's simple, just split the PRG and CHR of the 2 (or 4) games you want, them copy all the PRGs to a single file, do the same with the CHRs, paying attention to the sequence you used.<br />Next use the circuit of the thread I pointed, with the output on the upper address bus pins of the ROMs.<br /><br />You're limited to do multicarts with games that use the same mapper with this.<br />It's possible to do really nice ones with menus as Farid did <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8426" class="postlink">here.</a><br />But it's a bit more complicated, as you can see by going through the thread, but the end result is better.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7094">Fisher</a> — Wed Mar 21, 2018 5:50 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
